3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo calculates funding rates hourly using a time-weighted average price mechanism between the perpetual and spot markets. The exchange's rollup architecture enables sub-second order matching while maintaining on-chain settlement integrity. Funding payments occur every hour at the top of each hour, with rates determined by the premium/discount of the perpetual contract relative to the underlying OP spot price across multiple reference exchanges."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","OP","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OP/USDT represents a high-volume L2 token pair that frequently experiences funding rate imbalances due to narrative-driven trading around Ethereum scaling developments. The token's correlation with broader DeFi trends and rollup adoption creates predictable funding cycles, particularly during network upgrade announcements and ecosystem expansion phases."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OP/USDT on Aevo has shown consistent funding rate volatility ranging from -0.15% to +0.25% during major market events. The pair exhibits strong positive funding rates during Optimism ecosystem announcements and negative rates during broader crypto selloffs. Seasonal patterns emerge around quarterly OP token unlocks and major DeFi protocol launches on Optimism. Weekend funding rates typically compress due to reduced institutional activity, while weekday rates spike during U.S. trading hours."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's hourly funding settlements create frequent arbitrage windows, especially when rates diverge significantly from centralized exchanges like Binance or OKX. The rollup's fast execution enables rapid position adjustments to capture funding differentials exceeding 0.05%. Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes particularly profitable during OP ecosystem events when Aevo's funding rates can premium at 2-3x compared to traditional perps exchanges. Delta-neutral strategies work effectively given OP's active spot markets on both centralized and decentralized venues."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Trading OP perpetuals on Aevo requires careful attention to the platform's rollup dependency and potential validator set risks. Liquidity can thin during extreme market moves, leading to increased slippage and funding rate calculation anomalies. The exchange's combined options and perps model can create complex Greeks exposure if not properly hedged. Smart contract risks exist despite the on-chain settlement mechanism, and traders should monitor Aevo's rollup uptime and validator performance metrics closely."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are OP/USDT funding rates settled on Aevo?","answer":"Aevo settles funding rates every hour on the hour for OP/USDT perpetuals. This frequent settlement creates more arbitrage opportunities compared to the standard 8-hour cycles used by most centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What makes Aevo's OP funding rates different from other exchanges?","answer":"Aevo's rollup-based architecture and combined options/perps liquidity pool can create unique funding rate dynamics. The platform's focus on pre-launch and emerging tokens also attracts different trader demographics, potentially skewing OP funding rates during ecosystem developments."},{"question":"Can I hedge OP perpetuals with options on Aevo?","answer":"Yes, Aevo's unified platform allows complex hedging strategies using both OP perpetuals and options contracts. This enables sophisticated Greeks management and volatility arbitrage strategies not available on perps-only exchanges."},{"question":"What are the main risks of OP funding arbitrage on Aevo?","answer":"Key risks include rollup centralization concerns, potential smart contract vulnerabilities, and liquidity gaps during extreme market stress. Aevo's newer platform status also means less historical data for backtesting funding rate strategies compared to established exchanges."}]}]
